summary.span: 使基于 Windows 的应用程序可以从 Web 设置服务中检索用户设置。

span.span: Enables Windows-based applications to retrieve user settings from a Web settings service.

remarks.format: ## Remarks 你可以使用客户端应用程序服务通过配置应用程序使用从现有的 Web 设置服务中检索用户设置类。You can use client application services to retrieve user settings from an existing Web settings service by configuring your application to use the class. 有关详细信息，请参阅[如何：配置客户端应用程序服务](~/docs/framework/common-client-technologies/how-to-configure-client-application-services.md)。For more information, see [How to: Configure Client Application Services](~/docs/framework/common-client-technologies/how-to-configure-client-application-services.md). 完成配置后，你可以获取和设置用户设置，通过应用程序设置类派生自并配置为使用类。After configuration, you can get and set user settings through an application settings class derived from and configured to use the class. 你可以使用 Visual Studio 生成`Settings`为你的项目的类 (作为访问`Properties.Settings.Default`在 C# 和`My.Settings`在 Visual Basic 中)。You can use Visual Studio to generate a `Settings` class for your project (accessed as `Properties.Settings.Default` in C# and `My.Settings` in Visual Basic). 有关应用程序设置的详细信息，请参阅[应用程序设置概述](~/docs/framework/winforms/advanced/application-settings-overview.md)。For more information about application settings, see [Application Settings Overview](~/docs/framework/winforms/advanced/application-settings-overview.md). 你可以检索当前通过使用完全限定的属性类名称作为键。You can retrieve the current through the property using the fully-qualified class name as a key. 您还可以检索提供程序通过属性在处理时事件。You can also retrieve the provider through the property when you handle the event. > [!NOTE] > 此类包含在类级别应用于类的所有成员。This class contains a at the class level that applies to all remarks.format: ## Remarks 后设置提供程序访问设置服务，即使不成功保存这些设置时，会发生此事件。This event occurs after the settings provider accesses the settings service, even if the settings were not successfully saved. 提供程序可能无法保存设置，其中一个原因是当前用户如果已注销。你可以使用属性来确定是否已成功未保存任何设置。One reason that the provider might fail to save the settings is if the current user has been logged out. You can use the property to determine whether any settings were not successfully saved. 如果设置提供程序无法访问设置服务，而是将导致提供程序引发此事件不会发生。This event does not occur if the settings provider cannot access the settings service, which instead causes the provider to throw a . ## Examples 下面的代码示例演示如何使用此事件来显示未成功保存的设置的列表。The following example code demonstrates how to use this event to display a list of settings that were not successfully saved.
